      "raceComments": "{\"comment\":\"5. MAESTRO DU MESNIL was well supported for his handicap debut in latest and still managed to provide a good showing running 6.5L second despite not jumping fluently. Receives faster going and a step up in distance so is very much worth giving another chance. 6. CHURCHMAN is getting closer filling runner-up spots last two starts including one over course and distance. Can find a race of this nature. 4. BRAVE MOVE indicated ability finishing third of sixteen runners when last seen in December at Taunton (4800m). Arrives after a break and rates a danger if ready to go. 3. IAMYOUARE could have more to offer after just two attempts for this yard. Consider.\",\"runners\":[5,6,4,3],\"exclusive\":false}",
